4.3 Timeline Milestones
The Parties acknowledge the following operational stages for each Cooperation Result:

(a) identification of patentable result;
(b) written disclosure (within ten (10) business days of identification);
(c) preliminary ownership review (within fifteen (15) business days of disclosure);
(d) filing preparation (within twenty (20) business days of ownership confirmation);
(e) patent submission;
(f) office action response (within applicable statutory deadlines);
(g) grant, rejection, withdrawal, or abandonment;
(h) commercialization or licensing;
(i) enforcement or expiry.

The Parties shall agree in writing on specific deadlines, role allocation, evidence standards, and escalation workflow for each stage within thirty (30) days of the Effective Date, and shall update such agreement as needed. In the absence of a specific written agreement for a given stage, the Parties shall cooperate in good faith to meet applicable statutory deadlines.

7.1 Material Breach
A Party commits material breach of this Agreement if it:
(a) intentionally misrepresents or conceals inventorship evidence or contribution records;
(b) makes an unauthorized transfer, assignment, pledge, or abandonment of a Patent Right or Patent Application Right in violation of this Agreement;
(c) fails to comply with an ownership allocation confirmed in writing by both Parties or determined by a competent authority;
(d) fails to provide required cooperation documents within the timeframes specified in this Agreement after written notice and a ten (10) business day cure period; or
(e) materially breaches any other obligation under this Agreement and fails to cure such breach within thirty (30) days of written notice specifying the breach in reasonable detail.
